**Pattern**: Reflection/Generator-Critic
**Type**: Foundational + Quality Assurance
**Framework Support**: Google ADK (SequentialAgent), CrewAI (Multi-agent Crew)

**Key Characteristics**:
- **Self-Evaluation**: Built-in quality checks
- **Iterative Refinement**: Improves through feedback
- **Quality Thresholds**: Defined acceptance criteria
- **Transparent**: Clear reasoning for changes

**Business Value**:
- **Quality Assurance**: Consistent output standards
- **Error Reduction**: Self-correction before delivery
- **Compliance**: Policy enforcement
- **Auditability**: Documented improvement process

**Use Cases**:
- Contract negotiation
- Legal document generation
- Financial reporting
- Creative content review
- Code review
- Strategic planning
- High-stakes communications

**Real Example**:
LegalTech Solutions implemented reflection pattern for contract generation, achieving 78% automation rate, 95% compliance (up from 71%), and 6-hour turnaround (down from 3 days).

**When to Use**:
- Quality matters more than speed
- Mistakes are costly
- Compliance is critical
- Brand reputation at stake
- Multiple review rounds currently used
- Regulated industries

**Iteration Control**:
- **Max Iterations**: Prevent infinite loops
- **Quality Threshold**: Define "good enough"
- **Feedback Specificity**: Clear improvement guidance
- **Exit Conditions**: Multiple success criteria
- **Escalation**: Human review when threshold not met
